{"blocks":[{"key":"6band","text":" Mouse organ - 100 mg minimum (or closest you can come to that)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4eldr","text":"Plasma – 100 uL minimum - Make sure the plasma is settled in the bottom of the tube but not on the walls of the tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2nlh9","text":" Bacterial supernatant/spent/fresh media – 100 uL -- may need to dilute later","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1r3i7","text":"Brine or Food - 100 uL or 100 mg","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2r0ob","text":"ALWAYS MAKE – A Double blank – An HPLC vial with 1 mL Mobile phase A (no sample processing)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5v408","text":"ALWAYS MAKE – An extraction blank -- process an empty tube alongside your samples","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"12j8p","text":"ALWAYS MAKE – An ISTD blank – a blank with only an ISTD spike processed alongside your samples  Add 20 uL of “QRESS ISTD spiking stock”. Always want to add it before extraction to normalize for what happens to the sample during extraction","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9blq2","text":"Add  +   of QReSS IS spiking stock solution","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":7,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"20","error":false,"guid":"341C26A0BF2C11F0B1AD0A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":1}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"17p79","text":"Chill for 10+ min in freezer. Can chill overnight.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"am4b5","text":"Transfer supernatant to fresh labeled eppendorf.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9vck3","text":"Transfer 50 uL of solution to fresh labeled HPLC vial with insert.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1vomb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aloo2","text":"If your sample is a solid, perform beat beating for 1 min, chilling every 30 seconds.  After bead beating chill for 30 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8goje","text":"If you are using an aliquot of this for the NPH derivatization, take it now!!! ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8odn4","text":"NPH aliquot:  Add 50 uL to a second labeled Eppendorf.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
